[9] Florida (Broward County)
Date: Tue 23 Apr 2019 5:55 PM EDT
Source: WPTV [abridged, edited]
https://www.wptv.com/news/state/broward-county-measles-case-raises-concerns


One confirmed case of measles in an adult in Broward County is raising concern with health officials as cases continue to grow in other states around the country. The Broward measles case is the only one in Florida so far in 2019.

"Unfortunately it is a concern for us in the health care profession and the population in general," says Dr. Chad Sanborn at Palm Beach Children's Hospital. "A typical case can spread to up to 16 to 19 different people; it is very contagious," Dr. Sanborn says.

Parents held a rally on Tue [23 Apr 2019] at the state capitol against a bill that would allow the state to track individual vaccination decisions.

[Byline: Matt Sczesny]

