[19] New Zealand (Auckland): 11-month-old baby
Date: Wed 24 Apr 2019 10:19 NZST
Source: Stuff [abridged, edited]
https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/health/112227601/11monthold-baby-latest-measles-case-in-auckland


An 11-month-old baby has contracted measles, bringing the total number of cases in Auckland to 18. Auckland Regional Public Health Service (ARPHS) was notified of the case over Easter.

So far this year [2019], 10 people have been hospitalised for the disease in Auckland. As of Tuesday [23 Apr 2019] afternoon, 2 people were in quarantine and ARPHS has contacted, or is contacting, more than 1500 people who may have been exposed to measles.

ARPHS previously stated there were 18 cases, but one was later reclassified.

[Byline: Hannah Martin]

